      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WEST ON MENACE (1) was racing in great form recording two on end before she collided in the run and finishing sixth in a OPEN at this track (30.33). Better than last start and worth following up. JUST A MENACE (8) flew the lids with a strong early split and led throughout to score an impressive win by 0.8 lengths over 601m at this track (34.81). Deserves serious consideration again. CLEARY MAGIC (4) hit the ground running from a squeeze draw and prominent early but run ended and faded to finish 6th at this track in Free For All company. Form here at the trip sound including two wins. Strong form has emerged from her last run. Can do much better this time. BLACK TIGER (6) missed the placings here last start but is well-placed to turn the form around.",
